#: ../../../topics/spider-middleware.rst:222
msgid "DepthMiddleware"
msgstr "深中间件"

#: ../../../topics/spider-middleware.rst:229
msgid ""
"DepthMiddleware is used for tracking the depth of each Request inside the "
"site being scraped. It works by setting ``request.meta['depth'] = 0`` "
"whenever there is no value previously set (usually just the first Request) "
"and incrementing it by 1 otherwise."
msgstr ""
"DepthMiddleware 用于跟踪每个请求在被拆除的站点中的深度。它可以通过设置 "
"``request来操作。 eta['depth'] = 0`` 当没有之前设置的值 (通常只是第一个请求) "
"并以其他方式递增。"

#: ../../../topics/spider-middleware.rst:234
msgid ""
"It can be used to limit the maximum depth to scrape, control Request "
"priority based on their depth, and things like that."
msgstr ""
"它可以用来限制最大的深度到擦除，根据其深度控制请求优先级以及类似的情况。"

#: ../../../topics/spider-middleware.rst:237
msgid ""
"The :class:`DepthMiddleware` can be configured through the following "
"settings (see the settings documentation for more info):"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/spider-middleware.rst:240
msgid ""
":setting:`DEPTH_LIMIT` - The maximum depth that will be allowed to crawl for "
"any site. If zero, no limit will be imposed."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/spider-middleware.rst:242
msgid ""
":setting:`DEPTH_STATS_VERBOSE` - Whether to collect the number of requests "
"for each depth."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/spider-middleware.rst:244
msgid ""
":setting:`DEPTH_PRIORITY` - Whether to prioritize the requests based on "
"their depth."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/spider-middleware.rst:248
msgid "HttpErrorMiddleware"
msgstr "HttpErrorMiddleware"

#: ../../../topics/spider-middleware.rst:255
msgid ""
"Filter out unsuccessful (erroneous) HTTP responses so that spiders don't "
"have to deal with them, which (most of the time) imposes an overhead, "
"consumes more resources, and makes the spider logic more complex."
msgstr ""
"过滤不成功的HTTP响应(错误)，所以拼写器不必处理它们。 (大部分时间)造成间接费"
"用，消耗更多资源，并使螺旋逻辑更加复杂。"

#: ../../../topics/spider-middleware.rst:259
msgid ""
"According to the `HTTP standard`_, successful responses are those whose "
"status codes are in the 200-300 range."
msgstr "根据`HTTP标准`_'，成功的答复是其身份码在200-300范围内的那些人。"

#: ../../../topics/spider-middleware.rst:264
msgid ""
"If you still want to process response codes outside that range, you can "
"specify which response codes the spider is able to handle using the "
"``handle_httpstatus_list`` spider attribute or :setting:"
"`HTTPERROR_ALLOWED_CODES` setting."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/spider-middleware.rst:269
msgid ""
"For example, if you want your spider to handle 404 responses you can do this:"
msgstr "例如，如果你想要你的蜘蛛来处理404个回复，你可以这样做："

#: ../../../topics/spider-middleware.rst:272
msgid ""
"from scrapy.spiders import CrawlSpider\n"
"\n"
"\n"
"class MySpider(CrawlSpider):\n"
"    handle_httpstatus_list = [404]"
msgstr ""
"从 scrapy.spiders 导入 CrawlSpider\n"
"\n"
"\n"
"类MySpider(CrawlSpider):\n"
"    handle_httpstatus_list = [404]"

#: ../../../topics/spider-middleware.rst:284
msgid ""
"The ``handle_httpstatus_list`` key of :attr:`Request.meta <scrapy.Request."
"meta>` can also be used to specify which response codes to allow on a per-"
"request basis. You can also set the meta key ``handle_httpstatus_all`` to "
"``True`` if you want to allow any response code for a request, and ``False`` "
"to disable the effects of the ``handle_httpstatus_all`` key."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../topics/spider-middleware.rst:290
msgid ""
"Keep in mind, however, that it's usually a bad idea to handle non-200 "
"responses, unless you really know what you're doing."
msgstr ""
"然而，要记住，处理非200个响应通常是一个坏主意，除非你真的知道你在做什么。"

#: ../../../topics/spider-middleware.rst:293
msgid "For more information see: `HTTP Status Code Definitions`_."
msgstr "详情见：`HTTP Status Code Definitions`_。"

#: ../../../topics/spider-middleware.rst:298
